 Tsolo - Three men, aged between 20 and 25 years, are expected in court after they were arrested for murder on Tuesday at Gomeni locality in Tsolo at about 15h00. "The suspects were arrested by Tsolo Detectives after a 36-year-old man was reported by his father to have been last seen at Qebeyi locality in Tsolo on Friday the 13th of December, at about 18h00," said police spokesperson, Captain Dineo Koena. "During an intensive investigation, it transpired that one of the suspects was seen pushing a wheelbarrow to the nearby dongas where the deceased decomposed body was discovered. "The suspect was arrested and led police to the other two suspects." Capt Koena said that the motive for the killing is yet to be established. "The suspects will appear before the Tsolo Magistrate's Court soon." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 